{
  "buggy_files": ["sound/pci/hda/hda_intel.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["azx_resume"],
  "confidence": 0.9,
  "reasoning": "The bug is in azx_resume() which fails to reset chip->single_cmd (and chip->polling_mode) before calling azx_init_chip(). When codec communication times out during resume, azx_rirb_get_response() sets chip->single_cmd = 1 as a fallback. On subsequent resumes, azx_init_chip() checks 'if (!chip->single_cmd) azx_init_cmd_io(chip);' at line 1222, which means CORB/RIRB is never reinitialized once single_cmd mode is triggered. All codec communication then goes through the very slow single_cmd path (intended only for BIOS use), causing choppy audio with clicks and long silences. The fix requires resetting chip->single_cmd = 0 (and chip->polling_mode = 0) in azx_resume() before calling azx_init_chip(), so that CORB/RIRB is properly reestablished on each resume."
}

